1
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:42,542
{\an8}Trouble is normal in missions.

2
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:46,463
{\an8}<i>That's why what you need</i>
<i>is a reliable partner, like me.</i>

3
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:48,089
{\an8}<i>Are you still hiding</i>
<i>something from me, Dad?</i>

4
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:53,178
{\an8}Just keep your eyes open.
We are looking for Quebec Romero 1020.

5
00:00:53,261 --> 00:00:55,138
{\an8}That's the plate number
of the container van.

6
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:56,306
{\an8}<i>And if Mikoy is right,</i>

7
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:57,891
{\an8}<i>that would bring us to the secret hideout.</i>

8
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:09,110
{\an8}Agent Kian, go after them.

9
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:14,449
{\an8}She has shrapnel wounds
and some minor burns.

10
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:17,368
{\an8}And the doctor said they still
need to operate on Alex.

11
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:18,828
{\an8}Unfortunately,

12
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,705
{\an8}we've lost two lives already.

13
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:29,923
{\an8}Sir, I think Mikoy's just playing us.

14
00:01:39,349 --> 00:01:41,726
{\an8}How much more evidence do we need

15
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:43,978
{\an8}before you realize that
what I'm saying is true,

16
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:45,355
{\an8}that Mikoy is compromised?

17
00:01:58,368 --> 00:01:59,953
{\an8}We don't need any more reports

18
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:01,412
{\an8}or any debriefing,

19
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,164
{\an8}because what's the point of all that

20
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:04,958
{\an8}if the Moravianos keep
outsmarting us anyway?

21
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:06,167
{\an8}I think

22
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,752
{\an8}the problem is our office.

23
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:11,422
{\an8}The problem is the entire agency, sir.

24
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,497
{\an8}I don't like it when someone's
wasting my time.

25
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:52,130
{\an8}I'm here for you. To help you.

26
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,299
To talk to you.

27
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:08,104
I think we started on the wrong foot.

28
00:03:08,187 --> 00:03:10,023
I'm here to help you.

29
00:03:33,838 --> 00:03:37,050
These setbacks really are discouraging.

30
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:38,760
It lowers morale.

31
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:40,678
But we must soldier on.

32
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:42,931
- That's our job.
- No, sir.

33
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:05,536
I already warned you
about Mikoy several times.

34
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,372
That I think Mikoy is compromised

35
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,749
and anytime soon,
he will just turn against us.

36
00:04:09,832 --> 00:04:10,959
And what about Alex?

37
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:12,418
I already told you

38
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,504
how many times I've noticed
something's off with Alex.

39
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:15,922
She's not thinking straight anymore,

40
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:17,590
that Mikoy is manipulating her,

41
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,093
that I don't know what else

42
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:21,511
would make her believe.

43
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:23,930
And what did you do last time?

44
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:25,014
Did you listen to me?

45
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:26,641
You didn't listen to me, sir!

46
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:28,851
You thought I was just overreacting.

47
00:04:35,441 --> 00:04:38,695
And all of this happened
because of your negligence.

48
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:32,498
At first, of course,

49
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:34,167
I had my doubts.

50
00:05:34,917 --> 00:05:36,252
Maybe

51
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:40,048
they were just jealous of Mikoy.

52
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,518
Like they say,

53
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:56,105
"The more fruitful

54
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,357
a tree is,

55
00:05:59,275 --> 00:06:01,402
the more bashers it gets."

56
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:23,257
Sir Viktor, I'm just worried
about Mikoy's questions.

57
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:25,843
He doesn't miss any detail.

58
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:27,095
It's like he's investigating.

59
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:05,693
You know,

60
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:28,841
Easy there, son.

61
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:31,511
Are you okay?

62
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:34,388
Come on.

63
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:38,601
That choking fit was so dramatic, son.

64
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:39,560
Why?

65
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:40,978
I don't know.

66
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:44,941
Maybe that's why you're
trending everywhere right now?

67
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,693
What exactly did you do

68
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:51,197
to become everyone's
favorite gossip topic?

69
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,785
Wait, but…

70
00:08:56,869 --> 00:08:58,371
Is that saying still true until now?

71
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:00,873
That when you choke,

72
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:02,792
someone's talking about you.

73
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:05,211
What about politicians

74
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,213
who are in the headlines every day?

75
00:09:07,296 --> 00:09:08,923
Do they still choke too?

76
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:09,966
You're really something.

77
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:12,677
Isn't that what the elders say?

78
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,011
When you choke,

79
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:16,639
it means someone remembered you.

80
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,849
Or maybe

81
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,893
someone misses you, dear.

82
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:23,396
Hey!

83
00:09:23,479 --> 00:09:26,357
Chiara already misses him.

84
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:02,977
Son, why don't you call Chiara?

85
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,604
You know,

86
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:06,480
kids these days are so lucky, right?

87
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:08,399
As long as there's internet,

88
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:10,276
you can talk to your sweetheart,

89
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:12,653
no matter where they are in the world.

90
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,199
No, Mom, it's okay.

91
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,201
Chiara's busy too.

92
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,413
Why not?

93
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:24,498
We're just checking up on her.

94
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,584
We're not strangers to her, right?

95
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:33,215
You know, Mom. She has a lot
to take care of in Prague.

96
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,009
Maybe it's better

97
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:36,969
if we don't bother her for now.

98
00:10:37,053 --> 00:10:38,596
Is that so?

99
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:09,919
<i>You know, seeing Chiara</i>
<i>really lifts my mood.</i>

100
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:12,296
She has such a gentle face.

101
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,423
Such a kind child.

102
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:15,383
Right?

103
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:37,279
That's why La Morte Bianca sent me.

104
00:12:02,596 --> 00:12:06,600
I will be the one to kill him.

105
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:07,453
I needed to warn Mikoy
because Viktor was suspecting him.

106
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:08,412
No.

107
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,999
What you did was tell him that Chiara

108
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:13,083
is La Fornarina.

109
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:36,649
I will order the director
to remove you from this case,

110
00:13:36,732 --> 00:13:38,484
because clearly,
you're not listening anymore.

111
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,736
You are blind and deaf to the truth.

112
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:42,655
If you remove me from this case,

113
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,282
then you're also protecting
the Moravianos.

114
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:54,875
You're the one who should stand down.

115
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:56,377
Why don't you try?

116
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:59,547
Try to disarm me,
and let's see what happens.

117
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,302
Are you and Chiara having problems?

118
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:49,722
Or is Chiara the one who has a problem?

119
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,099
It's obvious.

120
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:56,270
Ever since you met
your handler that night,

121
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,484
you haven't been yourself.

122
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:07,489
Which could only mean

123
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,326
one of two things.

124
00:15:10,951 --> 00:15:13,370
Either your handler said

125
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:15,623
the world is ending tomorrow,

126
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,626
or they have information

127
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:21,629
about Chiara.

128
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:23,881
That could mean

129
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:26,967
she isn't innocent in all of this.

130
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:33,265
Dad, no offense, but…

131
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:37,811
I'm not comfortable
talking about this right now.

132
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:40,940
I'm not ready yet.

133
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:43,150
When will you ever be ready?

134
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,155
Son, if you keep bottling it up,

135
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:50,616
you'll only suffer more.

136
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:53,953
Look at you.

137
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:55,704
It's showing all over your face.

138
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:57,373
You can't sit still.

139
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,876
Your mind is always somewhere else.

140
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:03,295
Son,

141
00:16:05,255 --> 00:16:08,008
it's simple. Just face the truth.

142
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:09,969
That's unless…

143
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,181
you still believe

144
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:16,558
that Chiara is innocent.

145
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:20,938
That she's not part
of her family's syndicate.

146
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:25,818
Mikoy,

147
00:16:26,777 --> 00:16:28,487
the truth is right in front of you.

148
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,072
What are you waiting for?

149
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,825
You want the truth, Dad?

150
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:36,120
I don't care what Chiara is.

151
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,539
Because I love her.

152
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:40,791
I love her so much.

153
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,798
We're doomed.

154
00:16:52,302 --> 00:16:54,847
Looks like I'm not the only one
with nine lives here.

155
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:56,724
Agent Alex too.

156
00:16:56,807 --> 00:16:59,184
The doctors said she's incredibly lucky

157
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:01,353
because all of her injuries
are only superficial.

158
00:17:01,437 --> 00:17:04,690
That's why we need to be twice
or even three times more careful now.

159
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:06,775
Especially with Mikoy.

160
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:08,736
Mikoy, our asset?

161
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:09,820
Exactly!

162
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:13,157
Haven't you noticed?

163
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,409
He's turning all of us against each other.

164
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:21,623
No. All the intel he's giving us is dirty.

165
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:23,333
He's not the kind of person

166
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:26,003
who would knowingly
feed us dirty intelligence.

167
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:28,964
How sure are you about that?

168
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:31,425
I'm a profiler, remember?

169
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,393
But have you also considered

170
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:44,063
that maybe Viktor and the Moravianos

171
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:45,647
are just manipulating Mikoy?

172
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:53,947
So, what's your plan?

173
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:57,493
I really don't know, Dad.

174
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:02,414
So you're choosing Chiara.

175
00:18:08,837 --> 00:18:11,048
She's the one my heart chose.

176
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:25,979
I hope you realize
that your love has consequences.

177
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:29,274
If you keep turning a blind eye

178
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:33,612
to everything that family is doing,

179
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:36,031
you will become an accessory

180
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:40,494
to her crimes and her family's crimes.

181
00:18:40,577 --> 00:18:41,745
In the eyes of the G.A.G.O,

182
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,456
that's a form of connivance,

183
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:45,833
conspiracy,

184
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:48,418
and they will see you as a traitor

185
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:51,004
because you were supposed to be an asset

186
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:53,173
who defected.

187
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:59,096
Son, I understand your situation.

188
00:19:00,180 --> 00:19:01,932
I know how to love.

189
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:03,684
But

190
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:05,978
are you ready

191
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,356
for the huge and messy complications

192
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,859
that come with loving Chiara?

193
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,862
I hate to be the bearer of bad news,

194
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:18,031
but as your father,

195
00:19:20,242 --> 00:19:21,952
I have to tell you the truth.

196
00:19:39,094 --> 00:19:41,889
<i>Maybe they know he's an asset.</i>

197
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:47,686
That's what the Moravianos do best.

198
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,858
So we won't trust each other.

199
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:56,195
You know, you have a point.

200
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:00,449
As far as he's concerned,

201
00:20:00,991 --> 00:20:02,701
we can't trust Mikoy.

202
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:04,036
We can't do that.

203
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:07,706
So

204
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:10,083
we can tell him what's really happening.

205
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,313
Sir, you have a visitor.

206
00:20:31,396 --> 00:20:33,190
All right, let them in.

207
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:39,529
Sir.

208
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:45,994
As they say, when one door closes,

209
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:48,038
you enter through the sliding door.

210
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:52,834
Special Agent Sianong.

211
00:20:53,585 --> 00:20:55,087
Of course, I know you.

212
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:59,716
You're hardworking, dependable,

213
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:02,594
and most of all,
the most handsome one in this story.

214
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:11,728
Oh, well,

215
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:13,105
you know,

216
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:14,314
as they say,

217
00:21:14,398 --> 00:21:17,359
everything happens for a reason.

218
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:22,781
That's public service for you.

219
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:24,157
Some get hospitalized.

220
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:26,118
Some get promoted.

221
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:14,166
We've been avoiding each other
for so long.

222
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,585
Looks like we'll only reunite now.

223
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:22,716
What do you need?

224
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:26,344
I'm not asking for help, Norberto.

225
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:28,055
I'm collecting a debt.

226
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:30,849
What do you need?

227
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:38,899
Looks like he has a deep
and serious problem.

228
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:01,505
Why aren't we at the office?

229
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:03,632
Why here? What's this about?

230
00:23:03,715 --> 00:23:05,467
Listen to me carefully.

231
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:07,344
You're the only one I trust in the agency,

232
00:23:07,427 --> 00:23:08,345
and I need your help.

233
00:23:08,428 --> 00:23:09,888
This is making me nervous.

234
00:23:09,971 --> 00:23:12,057
If something happens to me,

235
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:14,559
promise me you'll make sure
that Mikoy stays safe.

236
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:16,144
Why? What's going on with Mikoy?

237
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:19,147
This isn't the first time
the Moravianos attacked me.

238
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:24,528
Is Mikoy really that important?

239
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:28,406
Why me?

240
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:29,616
Why not Agent Sianong?

241
00:23:29,699 --> 00:23:30,784
Just trust me.

242
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:32,202
Do what I'm asking you to do.

243
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,185
Hello? Who is this?

244
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:03,400
I don't have much time,
but I need to tell you this.

245
00:24:03,483 --> 00:24:05,235
Agent Alex is in the hospital.

246
00:24:05,318 --> 00:24:06,278
What?

247
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:08,071
Why? What happened?

248
00:24:08,155 --> 00:24:10,198
Remember the intel you gave us?

249
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:12,284
The one about Vertex's warehouse?

250
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:15,871
Well, turns out
it was a trap set by the Moravianos.

251
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:18,540
<i>They set Agent Alex up,</i>
<i>and when they got there,</i>

252
00:24:18,623 --> 00:24:20,083
a bomb was waiting for them.

253
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:21,751
Huh? What?

254
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:23,670
Wait. What happened to Alex?

255
00:24:23,753 --> 00:24:24,588
Is she okay?

256
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:27,716
Looks like the Moravianos
deliberately gave you bad intel.

257
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:29,467
Where's Alex? I'm going to see her.

258
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:30,760
No! You can't.

259
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:32,053
Why not?

260
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:33,805
<i>Because there's a bigger problem.</i>

261
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:36,975
Looks like the Moravianos know
you're an asset for the agency.

262
00:24:46,902 --> 00:24:49,738
Because I'm sure you're their next target.

263
00:25:00,916 --> 00:25:02,417
Before it's too late.

264
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:26,107
Bok!

265
00:25:27,317 --> 00:25:29,569
Wait. What are you doing? Bok.

266
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:31,655
I'm going to Mikoy. His life is in danger.

267
00:25:31,738 --> 00:25:33,073
Mikoy again?!

268
00:25:40,330 --> 00:25:42,374
<i>Because if he wanted to kill Mikoy,</i>

269
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:44,584
